                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.113,
                                "byte_start": 84045,
                                "byte_stop": 120512,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 98-1991, Public Lands Council versus Babbitt will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.113,
                        "stop": 199.549,
                        "byte_start": 120512,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.113,
                                "stop": 15.514,
                                "byte_start": 120512,
                                "byte_stop": 146112,
                                "text": "Much of the land on the Western Plains is public land."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.514,
                                "stop": 40.051,
                                "byte_start": 146112,
                                "byte_stop": 244332,
                                "text": "Ranchers have long used that land for grazing cattle and sheep and during the early 20th centuries, growing herds of livestock and increasing number of settlers led to conflict and the famous conflict between the sheepmen and the cowmen and between all the ranchers and settlers and among various other groups those who fenced it in and those who did not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.051,
                                "stop": 52.828,
                                "byte_start": 244332,
                                "byte_stop": 295428,
                                "text": "That conflict, and overgrazing, scarce water, and famous dust storms led Congress in 1934 to pass the Taylor Grazing Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.828,
                                "stop": 72.297,
                                "byte_start": 295428,
                                "byte_stop": 373273,
                                "text": "That law helped to preserve the public grazing lands by delegating considerable administrative power to the Secretary of the Interior in regularizing grazing practices to the Secretary\u0027s grant of grazing permits for grazing livestock on the public lands."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.297,
                                "stop": 82.033,
                                "byte_start": 373273,
                                "byte_stop": 412247,
                                "text": "Now the case before us involves some amendments that the Secretary made to the Taylor Act regulations in 1995."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.033,
                                "stop": 94.002,
                                "byte_start": 412247,
                                "byte_stop": 460104,
                                "text": "Groups primarily of ranchers or representing ranchers have challenged the lawfulness of three of those amendments, claiming that they exceed the Secretary\u0027s statutory authority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.002,
                                "stop": 116.988,
                                "byte_start": 460104,
                                "byte_stop": 552055,
                                "text": "One regulation changes the definition of grazing privileges, a second regulation deletes an earlier regulation\u2019s requirement that applicants had to be engaged in the livestock business, and the third one puts title to permanent range improvement such as fences and wells in the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.988,
                                "stop": 125.547,
                                "byte_start": 552055,
                                "byte_stop": 586327,
                                "text": "The Tenth Circuit upheld the lawfulness of all three of these new regulations, though by a divided vote in the case of two of them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.547,
                                "stop": 131.158,
                                "byte_start": 586327,
                                "byte_stop": 608688,
                                "text": "We considered the three and today we affirm the Tenth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.158,
                                "stop": 139.391,
                                "byte_start": 608688,
                                "byte_stop": 641707,
                                "text": "We explain why we hold the regulations lawful in our opinion, which is a little technical."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.391,
                                "stop": 163.975,
                                "byte_start": 641707,
                                "byte_stop": 740032,
                                "text": "We note throughout that opinion, but the Secretary has considerable authority to regulate grazing, but also we note that many of the adverse consequences that the ranchers fear including unfair departures from prior practice seem unlikely to follow merely from the regulatory amendments that we are considering."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.975,
                                "stop": 177.024,
                                "byte_start": 740032,
                                "byte_stop": 792172,
                                "text": "And in any event if those consequences did occur, individual affected ranchers would remain free to challenge the lawfulness of the regulations when applied to them, at that time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.024,
                                "stop": 193.943,
                                "byte_start": 792172,
                                "byte_stop": 859882,
                                "text": "The upshot is that we find as a general matter that the changes to \u201cone of the statutory requirements do not constitute a failure to adequately safeguard grazing privileges\u201d, they need the other relevant statutory requirement as well."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.943,
                                "stop": 195.808,
                                "byte_start": 859882,
                                "byte_stop": 867301,
                                "text": "Our opinion is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.808,
                                "stop": 199.549,
                                "byte_start": 867301,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice O\u2019 Connor has also filed a concurring opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
